data.description: MOTIVATED SELLER! This home could be yours for as little as 3% down WITH NO PMI! The seller will offer a concession to buy down the interest rate!    Just imagine owning this beautiful semi-detached 3-bedroom 2.5 bath home in sought-after Deanwood located on a quiet tree-lined street. Currently, the home is tenant-occupied and the tenant is in the process of moving. The home will be delivered vacant.   This wonderful 1548-square-foot home was renovated in 2015.  Upon entering the freshly painted interior, you are met with an open layout, and an inviting living and dining room. Passing through the living and dining room is a perfectly situated updated kitchen. The kitchen features a center island with a breakfast bar, stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, and plenty of storage making it easy for hosting dinner parties with direct access to the large rear deck.   Follow the refinished hardwood floors to the upper level with three graciously sized bedrooms and an updated full bath.  The primary bedroom features an ensuite, a large walk-in closet, and a balcony to sit and enjoy morning coffee. A hall bath and stacked Washer and Dryer complete the upper level.   The home has a fenced-in backyard and the ability to create off-street parking in the rear. The backyard is the perfect size to host friends and family on warm summer nights. Enjoy all the local amenities historic Deanwood has to offer. Located only half a mile and a 10-minute walk to Deanwood Metro Station.  914 46th Street provides a peaceful escape from city living, while just minutes away from Georgetown, Downtown DC, Capitol Hill, and easy access to both Reagan National and Baltimore Washington International Airports.
